item.title: CVE-2017-2853|2024-08-05T14:09:16.810Z -- natus%20medical%20incorporated -- natus
item.description: An exploitable Code Execution vulnerability exists in the RequestForPatientInfoEEGfile functionality of Natus Xltek NeuroWorks 8. A specially crafted network packet can cause a stack buffer overflow resulting in arbitrary command execution. An attacker can send a malicious packet to trigger this vulnerability.

item.title: CVE-2017-2861|2024-08-05T14:09:17.222Z -- natus%20medical%20incorporated -- natus
